      • max_index_size

        public int max_index_size
        Maximum amount of memory in bytes to use per stream for the index. If the needed index exceeds this size entries will be discarded as needed to maintain a smaller size. This can lead to slower or less accurate seeking (depends on demuxer). Demuxers for which a full in memory index is mandatory will ignore this. muxing : unused demuxing: set by user
